The paper discusses the learning of visual representations from natural videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of unsupervised learning methods is also a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of templates and the recognition of faces, which are topics that are often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
